"'''The Deposition of General Solo'''," originally titled "'''Deposition 9483749/12982 {Verbal}'''," is a short story in dialogue form, featured in ''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''. It was written by [[Kathy Tyers]] and [[Eric S. Trautmann]]. The story was later made available for reading on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Star Wars'' Hyperspace]] under the revised title.

==Plot summary==
[[General/Legends|General]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Judder Page/Legends|Page]] are debriefed by [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] and [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]] over their unauthorized decision to capture the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Emancipator|''Accuser'']] after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

